    "PoolBuilder depends_on PoolOptimizer (optional, $poolOptimizer)",
    "PoolBuilder depends_on SecurityAdvisoryPoolFilter (optional)",
    "PoolBuilder depends_on FilterListPoolFilter (optional)",
    "PoolBuilder depends_on EventDispatcher (optional)",

    "PoolOptimizer depends_on PolicyInterface (composition, $policy)",
    "PoolOptimizer uses Request (optimize() parameter)",
    "PoolOptimizer uses Pool (optimize() parameter+returns)",

    "Decisions depends_on Pool (composition, $pool, for literalToPackage)",
    "Decisions aggregates Rule[] (decisionQueue reasons)",

    "Problem aggregates Rule[] (reasons sections)",
    "Problem uses Pool (getPrettyString())",
    "Problem uses Request (getPrettyString())",

    "DefaultPolicy implements PolicyInterface",
    "DefaultPolicy uses Pool (selectPreferredPackages())"
  ],

  "key_patterns": [
    "DPLL/SAT solver: Solver.runSat() drives the main loop: propagate → selectAndInstall → setPropagateLearn → analyze → revert",
    "Pool is a value object (immutable post-construction) built by PoolBuilder and passed into Solver",
    "Decisions is a LIFO queue of (literal, level, reason-rule) tuples enabling backtracking via revertLast()/resetToOffset()",
    "PoolBuilder.buildPool() pipeline: load fixed/locked packages → batch-load required packages → filter security/abandoned/filterList → optimize with PoolOptimizer",
    "Transaction.calculateOperations() does a topological DFS over resultPackageMap to emit Install/Update/Uninstall/MarkAlias operations",
    "LockTransaction splits packages into dev/non-dev categories from Decisions output",
    "Problem accumulates Rules in sections for human-readable conflict reporting; static getMissingPackageReason() handles missing packages"
  ],

  "important_notes": "Solver.solve() returns LockTransaction (not Transaction directly). PoolBuilder.buildPool() runs three optional filter passes before returning Pool. DefaultPolicy caches selectPreferredPackages results per-pool. Request has three UPDATE_* constants controlling transitive dependency unlocking. Decisions iterates in reverse order (prev() in next()). Pool assigns sequential integer IDs to packages, used as SAT literals.",

